RACE.FOOTNOTES: LUMBERJACK stalked the leader keeping on the rail, rallied in the stretch to a driving win. UNDERCOVER ROWDY (IRE) set the pace and was outrun in the stretch. CONNECTICUT ran evenly but was never a factor. REAL FACTOR tired and pulled up before the last.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CAMDEN RACE 4 2 1/8M Hurdle CR: N/A. Handicap Purse 25000. TO BE RUN OVER NATIONAL FENCES FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH ARE RATED 115 OR LOWER. The highest rated horse will be assigned 158 lbs. with all other weights adjusted accordingly based on the current ratings. Minimum weight 140 lbs., not including a pprentice allowances.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: FIGHTINIRISHTABIT led from the start, drew clear in the stretch driving. PING PONG CHAMP settled in the rear first half and then rallied for second. CONNAGH'S QUAY pressed the pacesetter then tired and pulled up before the last hurdle.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: Carolina Cup Hurdle S. CAMDEN RACE 5 2 1/8M Hurdle CR: N/A. Stakes Purse 50000. TO BE RUN OVER NATIONAL FENCES FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON OVER HURDLES PRIOR TO MARCH 1, 2022 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES, OTHER THAN THREE YEAR OLD. Four-year-olds, 142 lbs.; older, 150 lbs. Winners, other than maiden, claim ing, starter or restricted three-year-old race: 3 lbs. extra for each race won.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CARAMELISED (GB) stalked the pace, drifted out after final fence, rallied and gained lead mid stretch, prevailed driving. WELSHMAN tracked the leader in second, took the lead two fences out and lead over the final fence, then overtaken mid stretch. STEP TO THE BAR set the pace, tired, and gave way. WHO'S COUNTING was no threat and trailed.
